Change-Id: I2d998f05f19693b70b28388117618f1d1f0e143d","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/eefadf660b2c119b32ddeca2804a35aff81e458c"},{"sha":"6d99767371d88c8a8ddcd4c91ea7a5681f68f59d","author":{"email":"808100943be7b7010123d78912f654820a5ee1c1@google.com","name":"Mehdi Amini"},"message":"Add a prettyprinter for mhlo.while operation

See the prettyprint test, the syntax looks like:

  %0:3 = mhlo.while(%iterArg = %cst_1, %iterArg_3 = %cst, %iterArg_4 = %cst_2) : tensor<i32>, tensor<i32>, tensor<i32>
   cond  {
    %1 = "mhlo.compare"(%iterArg, %iterArg_4) {comparison_direction = "LT"} : (tensor<i32>, tensor<i32>) -> tensor<i1>
    "mhlo.return"(%1) : (tensor<i1>) -> ()
  } do  {
    %1 = mhlo.add %iterArg, %cst_0 : tensor<i32>
    "mhlo.return"(%1, %iterArg_3, %iterArg_4) : (tensor<i32>, tensor<i32>, tensor<i32>) -> ()
  }

Change-Id: Iffe0020dd919d5797b63d5c9ff35548031b8d04d","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/6d99767371d88c8a8ddcd4c91ea7a5681f68f59d"},{"sha":"8390ed471b2e867c41627cabf0ab4f7eadb86e8f","author":{"email":"631d11d9fe908fc8f04b5865032c3043cb48fdfb@google.com","name":"Justin Lebar"},"message":"Allow nested instructions in HLO text format.

For example

```
ENTRY TestComputation {
    ROOT root = add(f32[10] parameter(0), multiply(f32[10] parameter(1), f32[10] parameter(2)))
}
```

This makes writing complex HLO text by hand easier, yay.

For now, we don't support nested instructions which have attributes (e.g.
`broadcast(x), dimensions={1}`) because the comma makes it ambiguous whether
the attribute is a new operand or not.
